        <h2>Storyline</h2>
        
        <div class="inline canwrap" itemprop="description">
            <p>
In present day Montreal, a famous Nicolo Bussotti violin, known as "the red violin," is being auctioned off. During the auction, we flash back to the creation of the violin in 17th century Italy, and follow the violin as it makes its way through an 18th century Austrian monastery, a violinist in 19th century Oxford, China during the Cultural Revolution, and back to Montreal, where a collector tries to establish the identity and the secrets of "the red violin."                <em class="nobr">Written by
<a href="/search/title?plot_author=Sean%20Gallagher%20%3Cnaes%40cgocable.net%3E&view=simple&sort=alpha&ref_=tt_stry_pl"
>Sean Gallagher &lt;naes@cgocable.net&gt;</a></em>            </p>
        </div>
        
        <span class="see-more inline"> 
                <a href="/title/tt0120802/plotsummary?ref_=tt_stry_pl"
>Plot Summary</a>
    <span>|</span>
        <a href="/title/tt0120802/synopsis?ref_=tt_stry_pl"
>Plot Synopsis</a>
    </span>
